contents:
攻下台北第一高峰！七星山步道、冷水坑、小油坑，親民路段收無敵視野 身為台北人怎麼可以不走一回「台北市第一高峰」，路途有趣、大景繁多、休憩點足夠，還有理由不造訪嗎？七星山較多人選擇的是「小油坑」或「冷水坑」兩個出入口，不管是搭公車還是自行開車要停車都較方便。
冷水坑：捷運劍潭站1號出口→捷運劍潭站(基河)→小15公車→冷水坑服務站。
小油坑：捷運士林站2號出口→士林官邸(中山)→260公車→陽明山總站→108公車→小油坑服務站。
劍潭捷運站的小15是大台的且可以站，所以很快就抵達冷水坑服務站，要往擎天崗的要跟司機拿轉乘票換車。這裡有廁所、飲水機，如果有想要臨時改去其他登山步道的，也可以在這裡詢問服務站的人員，非常方便。

Photography is an invaluable medium that allows us to capture the incandescent beauty of the outside world, something many of us haven’t seen in… well, a hot minute. Global pandemics will do that.
But that certainly doesn’t mean that beautiful photos can’t be taken indoors, out of windows, or in secluded outdoor locations (safely socially distanced, of course). And perhaps now is as good a time as any to gain some helpful tips on how to do just that by taking an online photography course.

Almost every day for the past nine or so months has felt like March 13, and that can sometimes make it difficult to want to wake up for the day ahead of you.
To make a morning person out of you, the wake-up light simulates the sunrise to gradually ease you awake. This allows you to wake up more naturally rather than being jolted awake by the default iPhone alarm sound, which honestly triggers my fight or flight response.
